<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 25 at 8:01PM MDT until August 25 at 8:15PM MDT by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 PM MDT
FOR SOUTH CENTRAL BEAVERHEAD COUNTY...
At 800 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Monida, or 28
miles northwest of Idmon Idaho, moving north at 20 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Monida, Snowline and Monida Pass.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
